ide\n        public void log(String message) {\n            // The task behavior under test does not depend on Ant project event logging.\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void log(String message, int messageLevel) {\n            // The task behavior under test does not depend on Ant project event logging.\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingUrlStreamHandler extends URLStreamHandler {\n        private final String content;\n        private RecordingURLConnection connection;\n\n        private RecordingUrlStreamHandler(String content) {\n            this.content = content;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected URLConnection openConnection(URL url) {\n            connection = new RecordingURLConnection(url, content);\n            return connection;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingURLConnection extends URLConnection {\n        private final byte[] content;\n        private String authorizationHeader;\n\n        private RecordingURLConnection(URL url, String content) {\n            super(url);\n            this.content = content.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void connect() {\n            connected = true;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void setRequestProperty(String key, String value) {\n            if (\"Authorization\".equals(key)) {\n                authorizationHeader = value;\n            }\n            super.setRequestProperty(key, value);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public InputStream getInputStream() {\n            return new ByteArrayInputStream(content);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Java test configuration**\n\nOkay, it seems like the Java test fails if the patch module doesn’t work, which exposes an issue in finding the class. If `Class.forName` fails, it falls back to returning base64, causing the assertion to fail. The user mentioned that tests must execute natively, so we need to configure the native build to include or load the required class. It seems the native build might already include reflection config and classpath, which could be okay, but do I really need no `Project.init`?\n\n**Evaluating native image build**\n\nI’m looking into native image builds, particularly how they use classpath and modulepath. There might be split package issues if a class in a named module exists. However, since the build succeeded with reflect-config's sun.misc, it seems that the class is present, which is good news! Now, it’s time to proceed with editing and refining things further. Let’s see how this all comes together!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0e79fc3ea7b47e140169eff924417481949732d8b2e60db27a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp7_kw5L4CjcInRvySMjtfilPhUwoWUFBA8Scre-RzkMRf5OzdS_0whr1MfOVUuw8sDC22sykFKNdvHZt9rs6OOlCMmC4vEyJyRyg-amnx-fBlJNazktCr0OpYM4TQH8jZSTJr9UmhGlYoHeYZAFW1jdE5214D2sfWIizuIM5SzkMVU9tsPn_n_o-xk7bqN5ZnLCIgmL9qlziIo3W-Jl_YQGzPh8_WDTRSwTHUPCAo-YoUGoyT5UxzTC_9uoRq6SKlEL24wv7CNoe5lkMPUQQ9w257OeMZZ_WcTdUkhVBn8sk1o3oGBYNVVEzlFlVTdgJf4EBkOZwpNx1ek3t-7LxyoUW-maC3Eump2l4ubyyGCVNwQ2Up6s8xAGBHNXwzSROBVmRF7Wq244BcmIopnZvjO3fw3QKXIgLMS7JZ4F5u54l6cWquPn8-vUKEEyxTW-9KJMP5aQobc4QgnQ8F8vufjQKsgr84-ho1d_jiY6E-RYgNrw9mzR2ewJkETVqz8WFk5kR6U9cyIuyW3F9OXtjDdAIs9BsT-bIZqRkWV2IwactnxMtxgq8POhkHq6cVX_u1n5qCNdgJmfbpF9t9Pchu0116IjdWKvKQdeDw9jALKYRC8_6JSWOJbW-RXsypmSL9WrcD_9t8Bu5NUrEFfbXmt80kP2ks-j98pR_OAjju9xjdL9UL2ldEi1Y7nqrkMfTWO65kRTSx7iraoA5ZJKCmaNlpR7AS783_xFb4woFzLSJQ7m_zqP7Ssc0WdWYeTvHbcB2t_uUz4oNzh2ig